TITLE: Printing Hello World in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This Rust code snippet demonstrates a basic 'Hello World' program. It includes a 'main' function that utilizes the 'println!' macro to output the string to the console. This is a straightforward example illustrating the syntax for function definition and output in Rust. No additional dependencies are required for this snippet; it's suitable for a command-line execution environment.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/introduction.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
# // This is a hidden line.\nfn main() {\n    println!(\"This is a code example\");\n}
```

