TITLE: Basic If-Else Conditional Branching in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Example showing a basic if-else if-else conditional structure for program flow control based on evaluating a variable, and another example showing assignment of a value based on an if condition.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/expressions/if-expr.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
# let x = 3;
if x == 4 {
    println!("x is four");
} else if x == 3 {
    println!("x is three");
} else {
    println!("x is something else");
}

let y = if 12 * 15 > 150 {
    "Bigger"
} else {
    "Smaller"
};
assert_eq!(y, "Bigger");
```

