TITLE: Refutable Pattern Matching in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the concept of refutable and irrefutable patterns, showing how different pattern matching scenarios behave
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/patterns.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
let (x, y) = (1, 2);               // "(x, y)" is an irrefutable pattern

if let (a, 3) = (1, 2) {           // "(a, 3)" is refutable, and will not match
    panic!("Shouldn't reach here");
} else if let (a, 4) = (3, 4) {    // "(a, 4)" is refutable, and will match
    println!("Matched ({}, 4)", a);
}
```

