TITLE: Illustrating Dyn-Incompatible Traits in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Examples of traits that are not compatible with trait objects, including associated constants, non-sized associated functions, and generic methods.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/items/traits.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
# use std::rc::Rc;
// Examples of dyn-incompatible traits.
trait DynIncompatible {
    const CONST: i32 = 1;  // ERROR: cannot have associated const

    fn foo() {}  // ERROR: associated function without Sized
    fn returns(&self) -> Self; // ERROR: Self in return type
    fn typed<T>(&self, x: T) {} // ERROR: has generic type parameters
    fn nested(self: Rc<Box<Self>>) {} // ERROR: nested receiver not yet supported
}

struct S;
impl DynIncompatible for S {
    fn returns(&self) -> Self { S }
}
let obj: Box<dyn DynIncompatible> = Box::new(S); // ERROR
```

