TITLE: Defining Generic Parameters Syntax
DESCRIPTION: This snippet describes the grammar rules for defining generic parameters in Rust, including syntax for lifetime, type, and const parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/items/generics.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
```grammar,items
GenericParams -> `<` ( GenericParam (`,` GenericParam)* `,`? )? `>`

GenericParam -> OuterAttribute* ( LifetimeParam | TypeParam | ConstParam )

LifetimeParam -> Lifetime ( `:` LifetimeBounds )?

TypeParam -> IDENTIFIER ( `:` TypeParamBounds? )? ( `=` Type )?

ConstParam ->
    `const` IDENTIFIER `:` Type
    ( `=` BlockExpression | IDENTIFIER | `-`?LiteralExpression )?
```
```

