TITLE: Overloading Compound Assignments Using Traits in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Explains how compound assignments can be syntactic sugar for trait function calls. The sample code defines an `AddAssign` trait implementation for a custom type. Understanding of Rust's trait system and operator overloading is necessary.
