TITLE: Using Constant Values in Inline Assembly - Rust
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to pass a constant value into inline assembly. It specifically showcases the usage of a constant expression to provide an immediate for an assembly instruction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/inline-assembly.md#2025-04-21_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
# #[cfg(target_arch = "x86_64")] {
// swizzle [0, 1, 2, 3] => [3, 2, 0, 1]
const SHUFFLE: u8 = 0b01_00_10_11;
let x: core::arch::x86_64::__m128 = unsafe { core::mem::transmute([0u32, 1u32, 2u32, 3u32]) };
let y: core::arch::x86_64::__m128;
// Pass a constant value into an instruction that expects an immediate like `pshufd`
safe {
    core::arch::asm!("pshufd {xmm}, {xmm}, {shuffle}",
        xmm = inlateout(xmm_reg) x=>y,
        shuffle = const SHUFFLE
    );
}
let y: [u32; 4] = unsafe { core::mem::transmute(y) };
assert_eq!(y, [3, 2, 0, 1]);
# }
```

