TITLE: Using Tags with Unions via FFI in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to combine unions and enums to implement a tagged union in Rust. It uses a structure to hold a tag and a union, allowing safe pattern matching based on the tag.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/items/unions.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
#[repr(u32)]
enum Tag { I, F }

#[repr(C)]
union U {
    i: i32,
    f: f32,
}

#[repr(C)]
struct Value {
    tag: Tag,
    u: U,
}

fn is_zero(v: Value) -> bool {
    unsafe {
        match v {
            Value { tag: Tag::I, u: U { i: 0 } } => true,
            Value { tag: Tag::F, u: U { f: num } } if num == 0.0 => true,
            _ => false,
        }
    }
}
```

