TITLE: Dropping a Tuple Captured by a Closure (Edition 2018 and Before)
DESCRIPTION: This code shows that in older editions of Rust, if a closure captures any part of a composite type, the whole type is captured. This means that the entire tuple is dropped when the closure is dropped, even if only one element of the tuple is explicitly used within the closure.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/types/closure.md#2025-04-21_snippet_28

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
```rust
{
    let tuple =
      (String::from("foo"), String::from("bar"));
    {
        let c = || { // --------------------------+
            // tuple is captured into the closure |
            drop(tuple.0); //                     |
        }; //                                     |
    } // 'c' and 'tuple' dropped here ------------+
}
```
```

