TITLE: Multiplying with Shifts and Adds using Inline Assembly in Rust
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using inline assembly to multiply a number by 6 using shifts and adds. The code uses the asm! macro to embed x86_64 assembly instructions within Rust code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/inline-assembly.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Rust
CODE:
```
use std::arch::asm;

// Multiply x by 6 using shifts and adds
let mut x: u64 = 4;
unsafe {
    asm!(
        "mov {tmp}, {x}",
        "shl {tmp}, 1",
        "shl {x}, 2",
        "add {x}, {tmp}",
        x = inout(reg) x,
        tmp = out(reg) _,
    );
}
assert_eq!(x, 4 * 6);
```

