TITLE: Defining Integer Literal Grammar in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This grammar defines the syntax for integer literals in Rust, including decimal, binary, octal, and hexadecimal representations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/tokens.md#2025-04-21_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: grammar
CODE:
```
INTEGER_LITERAL ->
    ( DEC_LITERAL | BIN_LITERAL | OCT_LITERAL | HEX_LITERAL ) SUFFIX_NO_E?

DEC_LITERAL -> DEC_DIGIT (DEC_DIGIT|`_`)*

BIN_LITERAL -> `0b` (BIN_DIGIT|`_`)* BIN_DIGIT (BIN_DIGIT|`_`)*

OCT_LITERAL -> `0o` (OCT_DIGIT|`_`)* OCT_DIGIT (OCT_DIGIT|`_`)*

HEX_LITERAL -> `0x` (HEX_DIGIT|`_`)* HEX_DIGIT (HEX_DIGIT|`_`)*

BIN_DIGIT -> [`0`-`1`]

OCT_DIGIT -> [`0`-`7`]

DEC_DIGIT -> [`0`-`9`]

HEX_DIGIT -> [`0`-`9` `a`-`f` `A`-`F`]
```

