TITLE: Demonstrating #[expect] Attribute Usage in Rust
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how the #[expect] attribute creates lint expectations. It demonstrates both fulfilled and unfulfilled expectations for the unused_variables lint.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rust-lang/reference.git/blob/master/src/attributes/diagnostics.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
fn main() {
    #[expect(unused_variables)]
    let question = "who lives in a pineapple under the sea?";
